    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="570"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Co-Chairman of the Anglo-American Caribbean
                        Commission</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_TCW1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Taussig</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-16">January 16,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">hongkong</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The President told <persName corresp="#p_SOFG1">Stanley</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d570fn1">The reference is to <persName corresp="#p_SOFG1"
                            >Oliver F. G. Stanley</persName>, the British Secretary of State for the
                        Colonies, who was in the process of discussing colonial problems with
                        officials of the Department of State; see Notter, <ref target="#pg_389">p.
                            389</ref>.</note> in detail of his discussions on Hongkong with
                        <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> at Cairo. Briefly—the
                    British to make a <hi rend="italic">beau gest</hi>[<hi rend="italic">e</hi>]:
                    announce the return of Hongkong to China; Ch[i]ang “or his successor” in three
                    days time to announce that Hongkong is a free port and open to the entire world
                    on equal terms; no one in Hongkong to be deprived of his property as of the
                    period prior to the Japanese invasion. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
